  "kind": "note",
  "title": "Aurelius, Meditations §aur_08_vii: Thou hast no time nor opportunity to read.",
  "body": "Thou hast no time nor opportunity to read. What then? Hast thou not time and opportunity to exercise thyself, not to wrong thyself; to strive against all carnal pleasures and pains, and to get the upper hand of them; to contemn honour and vainglory; and not only, not to be angry with them, whom towards thee thou doest find unsensible and unthankful; but also to have a care of them still, and of their welfare?",
